        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW (Peace)/8–2547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-25">August 25,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>741. Sobranje has just approved unanimously Cabinet decision ratify peace treaty.
                    Foreign Minister Georgiev<note n="1" xml:id="d351fn1">Kimon Georgiev, Bulgarian
                        Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs since November
                        1946.</note> who was first speaker extolled Soviet Union and said Bulgaria
                    through UN would seek amelioration treaty conditions imposed as result US and UK
                    pressure. Speakers for other parties including opposition then supported
                    ratification. In conclusion provisional president Kolarov<note n="2" xml:id="d351fn2">Vasil Petkov Kolarov, Acting President of Bulgaria since
                        1946.</note> reiterated Bulgaria’s intention seeking redress for alleged
                    injustices in treaty especially refusal recognize Bulgaria’s cobelligerency,
                    Bulgaria’s demand for Greek Thrace and reparations clause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
